t gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A massage gun is a tool that can provide a full-body massage and pre- or post-workout therapy, primarily designed for at-home or on-the-go usage and single-person handling.</p><p>It can also be found under different names, such as crossfit massage gun, portable massage gun, etc.</p><p>Most massage guns come with multiple attachments, which can do everything from switching up intensity levels, improving massage precision, targeting specific muscle groups, and so on.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1671119962228" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1671119962228"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">What are the Benefits of Using Massage Guns for Athletes?</span></h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670260049455" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670260049455"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Massage Guns are Therapeutic</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673192257752" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673192257752" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Massage guns promise to speed athletic recovery, increase circulation, decrease muscle pain and soreness, reduce inflammation, increase mobility, and similar benefits that result from regular massages.</p><p>They’re equally good at preparing your body with pre-workout muscle activation, easing muscle tension after a hard workout, or simply stimulating your blood flow.</p><p>Studies have shown that after just five minutes of pummeling, a massage gun <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7675623/" class="" target="_blank">increased calf muscle motion rage in healthy adult males</a>.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670260049451" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670260049451" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673204739092" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673204739092"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Massage Guns are Excellent Warm-Up Tools</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670260049456" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670260049456" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><div>Everybody knows the importance of regular warm-ups before moving on to exercising.</div><div><span style="letter-spacing: 0px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="letter-spacing: 0px;">Standard warm-up routines typically involve some cardio and stretching to help get your blood circulation up and boost your energy.</span><br></div><div><br></div><div>However, using a massage gun in your pre-workout routine can help you precisely activate the muscle groups you want to work on.</div><div><br></div><div>This is especially beneficial if you exercise with heavier loads and need to ensure you’re ready for it.</div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1671120057351" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1671120057351"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Massage Guns Ease Post-Workout and Injury Recovery</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670260049460" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670260049460"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Just as you can use it to warm up, you can also use your athletic massager gun for post-workout therapy.</p><p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4127040/" class="" target="_blank"><br></a></p><p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4127040/" class="" target="_blank">According to studies, vibration therapy - such as that achieved by massage guns - eases up muscle soreness and lessens the pain threshold</a>, which is especially beneficial if you have any post-workout pain, such as a sustained injury.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670780526876" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1670780526876" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/76c9ad2f-d969-41d9-a6df-900e94fcf4e9/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-massaging-her-bicep-with-massage-gun-torokhtiy.png" alt="athlete massaging her body with massage gun" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673192374669" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673192374669"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Massage Guns are Precise Tools</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673192394930" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673192394930"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Unlike other at-home massage tools, massage guns let you precisely target the muscles you want to work on without much effort.</p><p><br></p><p>For example, foam rollers are very popular because they’re cheap and get the job done.</p><p><br></p><p>But they require greater energy use, can force you into uncomfortable positions to hit certain muscles, and have a much higher risk of causing pain and harm.</p><p><br></p><p>Massage guns are precise, they can be used in whatever position makes you comfortable, and they can have additional precision and benefits with proper attachments.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673204879109" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673204879109"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Massage guns make you feel good&nbsp;</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673204885058" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673204885058"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>At the end of the day, any form of physical therapy will make you feel better and rest easier.</p><p><br></p><p>Massage guns are a great way to help yourself achieve a positive state of mind at the end of an intense workout, or even just a hard day in general.</p><p><br></p><p>Once you try it, you’ll always look forward to using it.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672085690004" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1672085690004"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">When Do You Need a Massage Gun?</span></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672085778231" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1672085778231"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Nearly anyone can use a massage gun for various reasons.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">As discussed, athletes can use them for pre- or post-workout routines.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">But even regular people can use them as well to relax their body, especially if they feel muscle pain or tension from, for example, sitting or sleeping uncomfortably.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Senior citizens can <a href="https://massagegunadvice.com/how-to-use-a-massage-gun/" class="" target="_blank">use them</a> to reinvigorate and activate their muscles, and they help with improving the blood flow as well.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">If you face chronic tight spots, sore muscles, or other soft-tissue complaints, using a massage gun will make your life easier.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Massage guns are <a href="https://www.bobandbrad.com/post/massage-guns-why-they-work-how-to-use-them-bob-and-brad-concur" class="" target="_blank">highly recommended by physical therapists</a>.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div